{"id":163903,"date":"2023-05-18T16:14:17","date_gmt":"2023-05-18T10:44:17","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/?p=163903"},"modified":"2023-05-18T18:27:29","modified_gmt":"2023-05-18T12:57:29","slug":"snehlata-panday","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/snehlata-panday\/","title":{"rendered":"Snehlata Panday Wiki, Age, Death, Husband, Family, Biography &amp; More"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>&nbsp;<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Pandey.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-163959\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Pandey.jpg\" alt=\"Snehlata Panday\" width=\"481\" height=\"358\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Pandey.jpg 800w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Pandey-300x223.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Pandey-768x571.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 481px) 100vw, 481px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<p>Snehlata Panday (1934-2021) was an Indian doctor, physician, and dietician, who had a wide experience in fitness &amp; nutrition for more than 30 years. Other than this, she was known for being the wife of <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sharad-panday\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sharad Panday<\/a> and the mother of Bollywood actors Chunky and <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/chikki-panday\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Chikki Panday<\/a>. She passed away on 10 July 2021 in Mumbai due to a prolonged illness at the age of 87.<\/p>\n<div id=\"ez-toc-container\" class=\"ez-toc-v2_0_62 counter-hierarchy ez-toc-counter ez-toc-custom ez-toc-container-direction\">\n<p class=\"ez-toc-title\">Contents<\/p>\n<label for=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bcdeb7e4e17\" class=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-label\"><span class=\"\"><span class=\"eztoc-hide\" style=\"display:none;\">Toggle<\/span><span class=\"ez-toc-icon-toggle-span\"><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" class=\"list-377408\" width=\"20px\" height=\"20px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\"><path d=\"M6 6H4v2h2V6zm14 0H8v2h12V6zM4 11h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2zM4 16h2v2H4v-2zm16 0H8v2h12v-2z\" fill=\"currentColor\"><\/path><\/svg><svg style=\"fill: #000000;color:#000000\" class=\"arrow-unsorted-368013\" xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2000\/svg\" width=\"10px\" height=\"10px\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" version=\"1.2\" baseProfile=\"tiny\"><path d=\"M18.2 9.3l-6.2-6.3-6.2 6.3c-.2.2-.3.4-.3.7s.1.5.3.7c.2.2.4.3.7.3h11c.3 0 .5-.1.7-.3.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7zM5.8 14.7l6.2 6.3 6.2-6.3c.2-.2.3-.5.3-.7s-.1-.5-.3-.7c-.2-.2-.4-.3-.7-.3h-11c-.3 0-.5.1-.7.3-.2.2-.3.5-.3.7s.1.5.3.7z\"\/><\/svg><\/span><\/span><\/label><input type=\"checkbox\"  id=\"ez-toc-cssicon-toggle-item-65bcdeb7e4e17\"  aria-label=\"Toggle\" \/><nav><ul class='ez-toc-list ez-toc-list-level-1 ' ><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-1\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/snehlata-panday\/#WikiBiography\" title=\"Wiki\/Biography\">Wiki\/Biography<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-2\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/snehlata-panday\/#Physical_Appearance\" title=\"Physical Appearance\">Physical Appearance<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-3\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/snehlata-panday\/#Family\" title=\"Family\">Family<\/a><ul class='ez-toc-list-level-3' ><li class='ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-4\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/snehlata-panday\/#Parents_Siblings\" title=\"Parents &amp; Siblings\">Parents &amp; Siblings<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/snehlata-panday\/#Husband_Children\" title=\"Husband &amp; Children\">Husband &amp; Children<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/snehlata-panday\/#Other_relatives\" title=\"Other relatives\u00a0\">Other relatives\u00a0<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-7\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/snehlata-panday\/#Career\" title=\"Career\">Career<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-8\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/snehlata-panday\/#Death\" title=\"Death\">Death<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-9\" href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/snehlata-panday\/#FactsTrivia\" title=\"Facts\/Trivia\">Facts\/Trivia<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"WikiBiography\"><\/span>Wiki\/Biography<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>Snehlata Panday was born on Thursday, 17 May 1934 while some sources claim that she was born on Sunday, 17 May 1936 (<strong>age 87 or 85 years; at the time of death<\/strong>).\u00a0<span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_163903_1_1\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[1]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_163903_1_1\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/timesofindia.indiatimes.com\/entertainment\/hindi\/bollywood\/news\/alanna-panday-remembers-her-late-grandmother-with-priceless-throwback-pictures-says-lost-one-of-my-favourite-humans\/articleshow\/84335466.cms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">The Times of India<\/a><\/span><\/span> <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_163903_1_2\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[2]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_163903_1_2\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.indiatoday.in\/movies\/celebrities\/story\/ananya-panday-s-grandmother-snehlata-dies-at-85-in-mumbai-1826565-2021-07-11\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">India Today<\/a><\/span><\/span> Her zodiac sign is Taurus. After graduating with an MBBS degree, she earned a diploma in Gynaecology and Obstetrics following which she did a diploma in Family Planning.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_164234\" style=\"width: 336px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/An-old-picture-of-Snehlata-Pandey.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-164234\" class=\" wp-image-164234\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/An-old-picture-of-Snehlata-Pandey.jpg\" alt=\"An old picture of Snehlata Pandey\" width=\"326\" height=\"285\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/An-old-picture-of-Snehlata-Pandey.jpg 687w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/An-old-picture-of-Snehlata-Pandey-300x262.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 326px) 100vw, 326px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-164234\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">An old picture of Snehlata Pandey<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Physical_Appearance\"><\/span>Physical Appearance<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p><strong>Height (approx.):<\/strong> 5&#8242; 6&#8243;<\/p>\n<p><strong>Hair Colour:\u00a0<\/strong>Light Red Copper Brown<\/p>\n<p><strong>Eye Colour: <\/strong>Dark Brown<\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Pandey-image.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-163949\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Pandey-image.jpg\" alt=\"Snehlata Pandey \" width=\"301\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Pandey-image.jpg 301w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Pandey-image-113x300.jpg 113w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 301px) 100vw, 301px\" \/><\/a><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Family\"><\/span>Family<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Parents_Siblings\"><\/span><strong>Parents &amp; Siblings<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>There is not much information about her family.<\/p>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Husband_Children\"><\/span><strong>Husband &amp; Children<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Her husband, <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sharad-panday\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sharad Panday<\/a> (1934-2004), was an Indian heart surgeon who was one of the surgeons who carried out the nation&#8217;s first heart transplant at the King Edward Memorial Hospital and Seth Gordhandas Sunderdas Medical College in Mumbai in 1968. On 8 November 2004, <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/sharad-panday\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Sharad Panday<\/a> passed away at his home in Mumbai at the age of 70.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_152121\" style=\"width: 357px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-family-picture-of-Chikki-Panday.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-152121\" class=\" wp-image-152121\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-family-picture-of-Chikki-Panday.jpg\" alt=\"Snehlata Panday with her family\" width=\"347\" height=\"370\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-family-picture-of-Chikki-Panday.jpg 732w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/03\/A-family-picture-of-Chikki-Panday-282x300.jpg 282w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 347px) 100vw, 347px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-152121\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Snehlata Panday with her family<\/p><\/div>\n<p>The couple has two sons, <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/chunky-panday\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Chunky Panday<\/a> and <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/chikki-panday\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Chikki Panday<\/a>. Sharad&#8217;s son <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/chunky-panday\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Chunky Panday<\/a> is a veteran Indian actor and businessman, who has mainly worked in Hindi and Bangladeshi films. <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/chikki-panday\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Chikki Panday<\/a> is an Indian businessman who co-founded the Akshara Foundation of Arts &amp; Learning, a non-profit organization that supports the education of underprivileged children. Chikki is a member of the Steel Consumers&#8217; Council as well as the Telephone Advisory Committees of the Ministry of Communication and Information Technology of India.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_100371\" style=\"width: 447px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/An-old-photo-of-Chunky-Panday-with-his-mother.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-100371\" class=\" wp-image-100371\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/An-old-photo-of-Chunky-Panday-with-his-mother.jpg\" alt=\"An old photo of Chunky Panday with Snehlata Panday\" width=\"437\" height=\"265\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/An-old-photo-of-Chunky-Panday-with-his-mother.jpg 500w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/04\/An-old-photo-of-Chunky-Panday-with-his-mother-300x182.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 437px) 100vw, 437px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-100371\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">An old photo of Chunky Panday with Snehlata Panday<\/p><\/div>\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Other_relatives\"><\/span><strong>Other relatives\u00a0<\/strong><span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n<p>Snehlata&#8217;s son <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/chikki-panday\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Chikki Panday<\/a> got married to Deanne Panday, a wellness coach and author, in 1994. Snehlata&#8217;s son <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/chunky-panday\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Chunky Panday<\/a> got married to the Indian costume designer\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/bhavana-pandey\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Bhavana Pandey<\/a> on 17 January 1998 after dating her for almost ten years. <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/ananya-pandey\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Ananya Pandey<\/a> (actress), Rysa Panday, <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/alanna-panday\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span class=\"_ap_link_preview\" data-preview-variation=\"recommendationPage\" data-attribute=\"Alanna Panday\" data-url=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/alanna-panday\/\">Alanna Panday<\/span><\/a> (social media influencer), and <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/ahaan-panday\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><span class=\"_ap_link_preview\" data-preview-variation=\"recommendationPage\" data-attribute=\"Ahaan Panday\" data-url=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/ahaan-panday\/\">Ahaan Panday<\/span><\/a> (actor and model) are Snehlata&#8217;s grandchildren.<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_156478\" style=\"width: 414px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/Sharad-Pandey-with-his-wife-sons-daughters-in-law-and-grandchildren.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-156478\" class=\" wp-image-156478\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/Sharad-Pandey-with-his-wife-sons-daughters-in-law-and-grandchildren.jpg\" alt=\"Snehlata Panday with her husband, sons, daughters-in-law, and grandchildren\" width=\"404\" height=\"331\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/Sharad-Pandey-with-his-wife-sons-daughters-in-law-and-grandchildren.jpg 732w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/Sharad-Pandey-with-his-wife-sons-daughters-in-law-and-grandchildren-300x246.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 404px) 100vw, 404px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-156478\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Snehlata Panday with her husband, sons, daughters-in-law, and grandchildren<\/p><\/div>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Career\"><\/span>Career<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>When Dr Snehlata Panday began her career, she observed that only 20% of the patients who required medical assistance were actually unwell whereas the remaining 80% of patients had medical issues that were almost always related to weight. After visiting several slimming centres in many countries, Dr Snehlata Panday co-founded a beauty parlour cum slimming centre, Slimelle, in Mumbai on 1 August 1974. At Slimelle, Snehlata worked as a weight-loss consultant-gynaecologist and provided her services to several socialites in Bandra and Bollywood celebrities including <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/rekha-actress\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Rekha<\/a>, Babita Kapoor, <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/jaya-bachchan\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Jaya Bachchan<\/a>, Meenakshi Sheshadri, <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/madhuri-dixit\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Madhuri Dixit<\/a>, <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/hema-malini\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Hema Malini<\/a>, and Vinod Khanna. Dr Panday acquired expertise in a number of paramedical disciplines over the years, including yoga, acupressure, reiki, and hypnosis. In addition to appearing on numerous TV programmes and discussion programmes in India and abroad, she has written extensively for a variety of newspapers as well as magazines. She received numerous job offers from abroad but continued her practice in Mumbai.<\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"Death\"><\/span>Death<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<p>She passed away in Mumbai due to a prolonged illness on 10 July 2021. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_163903_1_3\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[3]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_163903_1_3\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.indiatoday.in\/movies\/celebrities\/story\/ananya-panday-s-grandmother-snehlata-dies-at-85-in-mumbai-1826565-2021-07-11\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">India Today<\/a><\/span><\/span> According to some sources, she passed away due to a heart attack. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_163903_1_4\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[4]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_163903_1_4\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/indianexpress.com\/article\/entertainment\/bollywood\/chunky-panday-remembers-his-late-mother-7408826\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">The Indian Express<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"FactsTrivia\"><\/span>Facts\/Trivia<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n<ul>\n<li>She was often referred to by the names Snehlata Sharad Panday and Snehlata Pandey.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>When Snehlata was born, the doctors told her parents that she wouldn&#8217;t survive much longer as she had a defective heart valve.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Snehlata Panday had a deep interest in palm reading.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In 1997, she penned a book titled Slim Now Stay Slim.\n<p><div id=\"attachment_164113\" style=\"width: 258px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Cover-of-the-book-Slim-Now-and-Stay-Slim-by-Dr.-Snehlata-Panday-published-in-1997.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-164113\" class=\"wp-image-164113\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Cover-of-the-book-Slim-Now-and-Stay-Slim-by-Dr.-Snehlata-Panday-published-in-1997.jpg\" alt=\"Cover of the book 'Slim Now and Stay Slim' by Dr. Snehlata Panday\" width=\"248\" height=\"439\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Cover-of-the-book-Slim-Now-and-Stay-Slim-by-Dr.-Snehlata-Panday-published-in-1997.jpg 452w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Cover-of-the-book-Slim-Now-and-Stay-Slim-by-Dr.-Snehlata-Panday-published-in-1997-170x300.jpg 170w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 248px) 100vw, 248px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-164113\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Cover of the book &#8216;Slim Now and Stay Slim&#8217; by Dr. Snehlata Panday<\/p><\/div><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>In an interview, <a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/chunky-panday\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Chunky Panday<\/a> talked about his mother and said that he used to take his mother to shows and shootings abroad because he was afraid of his multiple girlfriends who might get angry if he didn&#8217;t take them instead. He recalled how he was often mocked for being a mama&#8217;s boy and said,\n<div>\n<div id=\"eaa_after_nth_p\" class=\"eaa-wrapper eaa_after_nth_p eaa_desktop\"><\/div>\n<\/div>\n<blockquote><p>I have travelled with her everywhere and I was known as a mama&#8217;s boy. Normally heroines used to take their mothers along with them while travelling for films, I was the only hero who travelled with his mom. And since I didn&#8217;t have a steady girlfriend, I used to take my mother everywhere. I am glad that she got to see the world with me.&#8221;<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_164235\" style=\"width: 386px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Chunky-Panday-with-Snehlata-Panday-during-his-young-days.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-164235\" class=\" wp-image-164235\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Chunky-Panday-with-Snehlata-Panday-during-his-young-days.jpg\" alt=\"Chunky Panday with Snehlata Panday during his young days\" width=\"376\" height=\"326\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Chunky-Panday-with-Snehlata-Panday-during-his-young-days.jpg 691w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Chunky-Panday-with-Snehlata-Panday-during-his-young-days-300x260.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 376px) 100vw, 376px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-164235\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Chunky Panday with Snehlata Panday during his young days<\/p><\/div><\/blockquote>\n<\/li>\n<li>Snehlata, who wanted to have a daughter, used to dress up her son Chunky as a girl till he was two years old. She even made him wear earrings. Talking about this in an interview, Chunky Panday laughed and said,<br \/>\n<blockquote><p>When I was born, she always wanted to have a daughter and she got a son. So, till the age of 2, she used to dress me up like a girl. I used to wear these lovely earnings and that&#8217;s why today when I go shopping, I normally pick up ladies clothes and the shopkeeper asks me if this is for my wife or for my daughter and I say, it&#8217;s for me.&#8221;<\/p><\/blockquote>\n<\/li>\n<li>She created the special &#8220;Rekha Diet&#8221; and introduced Rekha to aerobics and a healthy diet, which resulted in Rekha&#8217;s iconic body transformation. <span class=\"footnote_referrer relative\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"  on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false),footnotes_container_button_plus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=true),footnotes_container_button_minus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed, force=false)\"><sup id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_163903_1_5\" class=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text\">[5]<\/sup><\/a><span id=\"footnote_plugin_tooltip_text_163903_1_5\" class=\"footnote_tooltip position\" ><a href=\"https:\/\/www.deccanherald.com\/content\/29625\/at-55-rekha-still-engima.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Deccan Herald<\/a><\/span><\/span><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<ul>\n<li>After Snehlata&#8217;s demise, her granddaughter Ananya Panday penned a note and shared it on her Instagram post and said,<br \/>\n<blockquote><p>She worked every day up until the age of 85, going to work at 7 am in her block heels and red streaked hair.&#8221;<\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_164007\" style=\"width: 304px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Panday-with-her-granddaughter-Anannya-Pandey.jpg\"><img decoding=\"async\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-164007\" class=\"wp-image-164007\" src=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Panday-with-her-granddaughter-Anannya-Pandey.jpg\" alt=\"Snehlata Panday with her granddaughter Ananya Panday\" width=\"294\" height=\"294\" srcset=\"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Panday-with-her-granddaughter-Anannya-Pandey.jpg 600w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Panday-with-her-granddaughter-Anannya-Pandey-300x300.jpg 300w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Panday-with-her-granddaughter-Anannya-Pandey-150x150.jpg 150w, https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/05\/Snehlata-Panday-with-her-granddaughter-Anannya-Pandey-65x65.jpg 65w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 294px) 100vw, 294px\" \/><\/a><p id=\"caption-attachment-164007\" class=\"wp-caption-text\">Snehlata Panday with her granddaughter Ananya Panday<\/p><\/div><\/blockquote>\n<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<div class=\"489bcfb86580b123547338c91db0eff2\" data-index=\"3\" style=\"float: none; margin:3px 0 3px 0; text-align:center;\">\n<ins class=\"adsbygoogle\"\r\n     style=\"display:block\"\r\n     data-ad-format=\"autorelaxed\"\r\n     data-ad-client=\"ca-pub-6769524711517462\"\r\n     data-ad-slot=\"2473600074\"><\/ins>\n<\/div>\n\n<div style=\"font-size: 0px; height: 0px; line-height: 0px; margin: 0; padding: 0; clear: both;\"><\/div><div class=\"speaker-mute footnotes_reference_container\"> <div class=\"footnote_container_prepare\"><p><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_label_expand_163903_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_label pointer\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">References<\/span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_button_plus_163903_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">[+]<\/span><span><\/span><span role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\" id=\"footnotes_container_button_minus_163903_1\" class=\"footnote_reference_container_collapse_button collapsed\" on=\"tap:footnote_references_container_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_plus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed),footnotes_container_button_minus_163903_1.toggleClass(class=collapsed)\">[\u2212]<\/span><\/p><\/div> <div id=\"footnote_references_container_163903_1\" class=\"collapsed\"><table class=\"footnotes_table footnote-reference-container\"><caption class=\"accessibility\">References<\/caption> <tbody> \r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi pointer\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_163903_1_1\" class=\"footnote_backlink\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>1<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/timesofindia.indiatimes.com\/entertainment\/hindi\/bollywood\/news\/alanna-panday-remembers-her-late-grandmother-with-priceless-throwback-pictures-says-lost-one-of-my-favourite-humans\/articleshow\/84335466.cms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">The Times of India<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_163903_1_2\" class=\"footnote_backlink\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor_163903_1('footnote_plugin_tooltip_163903_1_2');\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>2,<\/a> <a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_163903_1_3\" class=\"footnote_backlink\" onclick=\"footnote_moveToAnchor_163903_1('footnote_plugin_tooltip_163903_1_3');\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>3<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.indiatoday.in\/movies\/celebrities\/story\/ananya-panday-s-grandmother-snehlata-dies-at-85-in-mumbai-1826565-2021-07-11\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">India Today<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi pointer\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_163903_1_4\" class=\"footnote_backlink\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>4<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/indianexpress.com\/article\/entertainment\/bollywood\/chunky-panday-remembers-his-late-mother-7408826\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">The Indian Express<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n<tr class=\"footnotes_plugin_reference_row\"> <th scope=\"row\" class=\"footnote_plugin_index_combi pointer\"><a id=\"footnote_plugin_reference_163903_1_5\" class=\"footnote_backlink\"><span class=\"footnote_index_arrow\">&#8593;<\/span>5<\/a><\/th> <td class=\"footnote_plugin_text\"><a href=\"https:\/\/www.deccanherald.com\/content\/29625\/at-55-rekha-still-engima.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\">Deccan Herald<\/a><\/td><\/tr>\r\n\r\n <\/tbody> <\/table> <\/div><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>&nbsp; Snehlata Panday (1934-2021) was an Indian doctor, physician, and dietician, who had a wide experience in fitness &amp; nutrition for more than 30 years. Other than this, she was known for being the wife of Sharad Panday and the mother of Bollywood actors Chunky and Chikki Panday. She passed away on 10 July 2021 in Mumbai due to a prolonged illness at the age of 87. Wiki\/Biography Snehlata Panday was born on Thursday, 17 May 1934 while some sources claim that she was born on Sunday, 17 May 1936 (age 87 or 85 years; at the time of death).\u00a0The <\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":60,"featured_media":163959,"comment_status":"open","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[3],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/163903"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/60"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=163903"}],"version-history":[{"count":4,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/163903\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":164236,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/163903\/revisions\/164236"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/163959"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=163903"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=163903"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/wikibio.in\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=163903"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}